45 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
46 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
47 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
48 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
49 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
50 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
51  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
52 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
53 #else
54 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
55 #endif
56 #endif
57 
58 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
59 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
60 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
61 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
62 #else
63 #error "unknown compiler"
64 #endif
65 
66 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
67 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
68 #else
69 #include <cstdio>
70 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
71  do { \
72  fputs(msg, stderr); \
73  DNNL_TRAP(); \
74  } while (0)
75 #endif

86 
91 struct error : public std::exception {
92  dnnl_status_t status;
93  const char *message;
94 
99  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
100  : status(status), message(message) {}
101 
103  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
104 
110  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
111  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
112  }
113 };
114 
116 template <typename T>
117 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
118  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
119  const int size = (int)v.size();
120  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
121  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
122 }
124 
126 template <typename T>
127 struct handle_traits {};
128 
142 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
143 struct handle {
144 private:
145  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
146  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
147 
148 protected:
149  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
150  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
151 
152 public:
160  handle() = default;
161 
163  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
165  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
167  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
169  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
170 
176  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
177 
183  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
184  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
185  }
186 
192  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
193  T result = data_.get();
194  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
195  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
196  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
197  return result;
198  }
199 
204  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
205 
209  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
210 
217  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
218  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
219  }
220 
227  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
228 };

376 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
377  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
378  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
379  // returns a C type.
380  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
381  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
382  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
383  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
384  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
385 }

643 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
644  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
645  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
646  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
647  } \
648 \
649  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
650  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
651  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
652  } \
653 \
654  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
655  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
656  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
657  } \
658 \
659  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
660  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
661  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
662  return lhs; \
663  } \
664 \
665  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
666  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
667  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
668  return lhs; \
669  } \
670 \
671  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
672  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
673  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
674  return lhs; \
675  } \
676 \
677  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
678  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
679  }
680 
681 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
682 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

840 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
841  friend struct primitive;
842  friend struct reorder;
843 
845  enum class kind {
847  any = dnnl_any_engine,
849  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
851  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
852  };
853 
854  using handle::handle;
855 
858  engine() = default;
859 
864  static size_t get_count(kind akind) {
865  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(akind));
866  }
867 
873  engine(kind akind, size_t index) {
874  dnnl_engine_t engine;
875  error::wrap_c_api(
876  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(akind), index),
877  "could not create an engine");
878  reset(engine);
879  }
880 
881 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
882  engine(kind akind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
889  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
890  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(&c_engine, convert_to_c(akind),
891  device, context),
892  "could not create an engine");
893  reset(c_engine);
894  }
895 #endif
896 
901  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
902  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
903  error::wrap_c_api(
904  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
905  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
906  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
907  reset(c_engine, true);
908  }
909 
912  kind get_kind() const {
913  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
914  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
915  "could not get kind of an engine");
916  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
917  }
918 
919 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
920  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
923  cl_context context = nullptr;
924  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
925  "could not get an OpenCL context from an engine");
926  return context;
927  }
928 
931  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
932  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
933  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
934  "could not get an OpenCL device from an engine");
935  return device;
936  }
937 #endif

944  template <typename primitive_desc>
945  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
946  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
947  }
948 
949 private:
950  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind akind) {
951  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(akind);
952  }
953 
954  template <typename primitive_desc>
955  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
956  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
957  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
958  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
959  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
960  return engine(c_engine, true);
961  }
962 };

1039 #endif
1040 };
1041 
1043 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1044  using handle::handle;
1045 
1047  enum class flags : unsigned {
1050  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1052  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1054  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1056  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1057  };
1058 
1061  stream() = default;
1062 
1069  stream(const engine &aengine, flags aflags = flags::default_flags,
1070  const stream_attr &attr = stream_attr()) {
1071  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1072  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_v2(&stream, aengine.get(),
1073  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(aflags),
1074  attr.get(true)),
1075  "could not create a stream");
1076  reset(stream);
1077  }
1078 
1079 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1080  stream(const engine &aengine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1085  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1086  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, aengine.get(), queue),
1087  "could not create a stream");
1088  reset(stream);
1089  }
1090 
1093  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1094  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1095  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1096  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1097  return queue;
1098  }
1099 #endif
1100 
1103  stream &wait() {
1104  error::wrap_c_api(
1105  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1106  return *this;
1107  }
1108 };
1109 
1110 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(stream::flags)

1752 
1754  struct desc {
1755  friend struct memory;
1757  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1758 
1761  desc() : data() {}
1762 
1778  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag,
1779  bool allow_empty = false)
1780  : data() {
1781  validate_dims(adims);
1782  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1783  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
1784  convert_to_c(aformat_tag));
1785  if (!allow_empty)
1786  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1787  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
1788  "format tag");
1789  }
1790 
1806  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &strides,
1807  bool allow_empty = false)
1808  : data() {
1809  validate_dims(adims);
1810  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)adims.size());
1811  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1812  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
1813  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
1814  if (!allow_empty)
1815  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1816  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
1817  "strides");
1818  }
1819 
1823  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1824 
1827  //
1836  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets,
1837  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1838  validate_dims(adims, data.ndims);
1839  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
1840  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1841  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1842  &sub_md, &data, adims.data(), offsets.data());
1843  if (!allow_empty)
1844  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
1845  return desc(sub_md);
1846  }
1847 
1892  desc reshape(const dims &adims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1893  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(adims, 1);
1894  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1895  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
1896  &out_md, &data, (int)adims.size(), adims.data());
1897  if (!allow_empty)
1898  error::wrap_c_api(
1899  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1900  return desc(out_md);
1901  }
1902 
1939  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
1940  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1941  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
1942  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1943  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
1944  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
1945  if (!allow_empty)
1946  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1947  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
1948  return desc(out_md);
1949  }
1950 
1955  memory::dims dims() const {
1956  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
1957  }
1958 
1961  memory::data_type data_type() const {
1962  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
1963  }
1964 
1969  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1970 
1974  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1975 
1980  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1981  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1982  }
1983 
1988  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1989 
1993  explicit operator bool() const { return data.ndims != 0; }
1994  };
1995 
2000  memory() = default;
2001

2026  "could not create a memory object");
2027  reset(result);
2028  }

2897  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2898  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2899  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2900  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2901  query::exec_arg_md};
2902  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2903  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2904  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2905  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2906 
2907  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2908  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2909  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2910  }

2919  }

3051  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
3052  "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3053  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
3054  }
3055 
3056 protected:
3060  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
3061  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
3062  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
3063  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");
3064  reset(new_pd);
3065  }
3066 
3080  primitive_desc_base(
3081  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3082  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3083 
3095  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3096  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind aprop_kind)
3097  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, aprop_kind, aprop_kind) {}
3098 
3112  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3113  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3114  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3115  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3116  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3117 
3118  dnnl_status_t rc;
3119 
3120  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3121  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3122  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3123 
3124  // Check that primitive kind matches
3125  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3126  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3127  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3128  error::wrap_c_api(
3129  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3130  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3131  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3132  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3133 
3134  // Check that propagation kind matches
3135  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3136  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3137  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3138 
3139  // Something went wrong
3140  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3141  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3142  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3143  "descriptor");
3144 
3145  // Everything is fine
3146  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3147  || (rc == dnnl_success
3148  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3149  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3150  reset_with_clone(pd);
3151  return;
3152  }
3153 
3154  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3155  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3156  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3157  }
3158 
3159  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3160 };
3161

3174 struct reorder : public primitive {

3181 
3199  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,
3200  const engine &dst_engine, const memory::desc &dst_md,
3201  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr(),
3202  bool allow_empty = false) {

3233  dst.get_engine().get(), attr.get());
3234  if (!allow_empty)

3236  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a reorder "

3238  reset(status == dnnl_success ? result : dnnl_primitive_desc_t());
3239  }

3309 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3310  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
3311  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
3312  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());
3313  for (const auto &s : mems)
3314  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
3315  return c_mems;
3316 }

3503 
3506 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3507  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3508 
3509  primitive_desc() = default;
3510 
3533  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3534  const engine &aengine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3535  bool allow_empty = false)
3536  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3537  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3538  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3539  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, aengine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3540  if (!allow_empty)
3541  error::wrap_c_api(
3542  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3543  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3544  fetch_impl();
3545  }
3546 
3551  bool next_impl() {
3552  dnnl_status_t status
3553  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3554  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3555  error::wrap_c_api(
3556  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3557  fetch_impl();
3558  return true;
3559  }
3560 
3561 private:
3562  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3563  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3564  void fetch_impl() {
3565  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3566  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3567  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3568  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3569  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3570  "descriptor iterator");
3571  reset(pd);
3572  }
3573 };

6200  private:

6205  memory::desc stat_desc(int kind) const {

6207  error::wrap_c_api(

6210  &p),

7221  return base::query_md(query::exec_arg_md, DNNL_ARG_DIFF_DST_ITER_C);
7222  }
7223 
7224 protected:
7225  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7226 
7227  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7228  //
7229  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7230  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7231  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7232  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7233  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7234  //
7235  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7236  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7237  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7238  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7239  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7240  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7241  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7242  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7243  dnnl_status_t rc;
7244  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7245  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7246  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7247  "for an RNN primitive");
7248 
7249  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7250  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7251  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7252 
7253  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7254  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7255  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7256  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7257 
7258  if (!ok)
7259  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7260  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7261  "RNN primitive");
7262 
7263  reset_with_clone(pd);
7264  }
7265 };
7266 
7268 struct vanilla_rnn_forward : public primitive {
7270  struct desc {
7271  dnnl_rnn_desc_t data;
7272 
7313  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm activation,
7314  rnn_direction direction, const memory::desc &src_layer_desc,
7315  const memory::desc &src_iter_desc,

9545 
9550  primitive_desc(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd)
9551  : dnnl::primitive_desc(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::matmul) {}
9552 
9554  memory::desc src_desc() const { return query_md(query::src_md, 0); }
9555 
9557  memory::desc weights_desc() const {
9558  return query_md(query::weights_md, 0);
9559  }
9560 
9562  memory::desc bias_desc() const {
9563  return query_md(query::weights_md, 1);
9564  }
9565 
9567  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return query_md(query::dst_md, 0); }
9568  };
9569 
9571  matmul() = default;
9572 
9575  matmul(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd) {}
9576 };

9591 struct resampling_forward : public primitive {
9593  struct desc {
9594  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
9595 
9611  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9612  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
9613  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9614  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9615  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), nullptr,
9616  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
9617  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9618  }
9619 
9631  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9632  const std::vector<float> &factors,
9633  const memory::desc &src_desc) {
9634  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
9635  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9636  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9637  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), &factors[0],
9638  &src_desc.data, nullptr),
9639  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9640  }
9641 
9658  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9659  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
9660  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
9661  if (!factors.empty())
9662  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
9663  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9664  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9665  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), factors.data(),
9666  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
9667  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9668  }
9669  };

9735 struct resampling_backward : public primitive {
9737  struct desc {
9738  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
9739 
9748  desc(algorithm aalgorithm, const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
9749  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
9750  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
9751  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), nullptr,
9752  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
9753  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
9754  }
9755 
9765  desc(algorithm aalgorithm, const std::vector<float> &factors,
9766  const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
9767  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
9768  if (!factors.empty())
9769  memory::validate_dims(factors, diff_src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
9770  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
9771  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), factors.data(),
9772  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
9773  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
9774  }

10039 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &astream,
10040  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10041  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10042  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10043  for (const auto &a : args)
10044  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10045 
10046  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), astream.get(),
10047  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10048  "could not execute a primitive");
10049 }
